\end_inset

 Consider the following proposition: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
(A\sledi B)\inn(B\sledi C)\inn(\neg A\ali C)
\]

\end_inset

We computed its truth table in Chapter 
\begin_inset Formula $1.2$
\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{tabular}{c|c|c|c|c}
\hline  %after
 &  \ensuremath{A}  &  \ensuremath{B}  &  \ensuremath{C}  &  \ensuremath{(A\sledi B)\inn(B\sledi C)\inn(\neg A\ali C)}\\
\hline  1.  &  1  &  1  &  1  &  1 \\
 2.  &  1  &  1  &  0  &  0 \\
 3.  &  1  &  0  &  1  &  0 \\
 4.  &  1  &  0  &  0  &  0 \\
 5.  &  0  &  1  &  1  &  1 \\
 6.  &  0  &  1  &  0  &  0 \\
 7.  &  0  &  0  &  1  &  1 \\
 8.  &  0  &  0  &  0  &  1 \\
  &   &   &  
\end{tabular}
\]

\end_inset

In the previous chapter we wrote this proposition in its canonical DNF as:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
(A\inn B\inn C)\ali(\neg A\inn B\inn C)\ali(\neg A\inn\neg B\inn C)\ali(\neg A\inn\neg B\inn\neg C)\,.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This form corresponds to the following circuit: 
\begin_inset Float figure
placement h!
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

