\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore, a single proposition can be represented by more than one switching
 circuit.
 It is therefore reasonable to require that, in the actual physical construction
 of circuits simulating a given proposition, our goal is to find a circuit
 as simple as possible.
 Perhaps the circuit should also satisfy certain other requirements (depending
 on the application).
 We will not consider these issues here.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


