\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-greatest lower bound (
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-infimum)
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 of a subset 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\cee$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 is an 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-lower bound for 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 and for every 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-lower bound 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

