\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 it holds 
\begin_inset Formula $xRa$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Notation: 
\begin_inset Formula $a=R$
\end_inset

-
\begin_inset Formula $\inf U$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $b\in S$
\end_inset

 is an 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

{
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
em
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-least upper bound (
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-supremum)
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 of a subset 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\cee$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 is an 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-upper bound for 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 and for every 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-upper bound 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

