\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Remark:
\series default
 The definitions of immediate successor and 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-greatest element can also be introduced for general partially ordered sets.
 But they are particularly interesting for well ordered sets, since the
 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-greatest elements are the only elements without an immediate successor
 (as we will see below).
 In general partially ordered sets this may not be the case: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename Hasse3-en.eps
	height 30mm

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{prop}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 be a well ordering on 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 and let 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in S$
\end_inset

.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 is not the 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-greatest element of the set 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 has a unique immediate successor.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{prop}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Consider the set 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
X=\{z~;z\in S\inn xRz\}\,.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 is not 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-last, the set 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is nonempty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore, set 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 has a unique 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-least element 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let us show that 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 is an immediate successor of 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Since 
\begin_inset Formula $y\in X$
\end_inset

, we have 
\begin_inset Formula $xRy$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If 
\begin_inset Formula $z\in S$
\end_inset

 is an element such that 
\begin_inset Formula $xRz$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $z\neq y$
\end_inset

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $yRz$
\end_inset

 (since 
\begin_inset Formula $z\in X$
\end_inset

 and is 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-least element of set 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 is also unique immediate successor of element 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Suppose that there exists 
\begin_inset Formula $z\neq y$
\end_inset

 that is an immediate successor of 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $xRz$
\end_inset

, we have 
\begin_inset Formula $z\in X$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-least element of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $z\in X\inn z\neq y$
\end_inset

, it also holds 
\begin_inset Formula $yRz$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But this is a contradiction with the definition of immediate successor of
 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The notion of immediate predecessor is defined similarly as the notion of
 immediate successor.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
However the analogous claim for a well order 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

, saying that every element 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 that is not 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-least has (a unique) immediate successor, does not hold!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset

 
\series bold
Example:
\series default
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $S=\mathbb{N}\cup\{\infty\}$
\end_inset

.
 For 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 take the usual ordering 
\begin_inset Formula $<$
\end_inset

 on 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{N}$
\end_inset

, extended by the rule 
\begin_inset Formula $n<\infty$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $n\in\mathbb{N}$
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 well orders 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

.
 However, element 
\begin_inset Formula $\infty$
\end_inset

 does not have any immediate predecessors.
\end_layout

